# ATTACK 4 — Clickjacking

## What is it?
Attacker embeds your legitimate website in a hidden `<iframe>` on their page.  
They place transparent UI over it — victim thinks they're clicking attacker's button, actually clicking your app's button underneath.

```
Attacker's page (what victim sees):    Your app in hidden iframe (what actually gets clicked):
┌──────────────────────────┐           ┌──────────────────────────┐
│  WIN A FREE IPHONE!      │           │  [invisible]             │
│                          │           │                          │
│  [CLICK HERE TO CLAIM]   │  ←─────── │  [Delete Account]        │
└──────────────────────────┘           └──────────────────────────┘
opacity: 0 on iframe, positioned exactly behind "CLICK HERE" button
```

### Protection
```js
// ✅ X-Frame-Options header — prevents your site from being iframed
// In Express with Helmet:
app.use(helmet({ frameguard: { action: 'deny' } }));
// Sends: X-Frame-Options: DENY

// ✅ Content-Security-Policy frame-ancestors (modern, more flexible)
// In Nginx:
add_header Content-Security-Policy "frame-ancestors 'none'";

// Allow only your own domain to iframe:
add_header Content-Security-Policy "frame-ancestors 'self' https://dashboard.yourapp.com";

// ✅ JavaScript frame-busting (legacy fallback)
if (window.top !== window.self) {
  window.top.location = window.self.location;
}
```

