# ATTACK 8 — Open Redirect

## What is it?
App redirects users to a URL provided in a parameter — attacker crafts URL that redirects to phishing site.

```
Legitimate feature: After login, redirect to where user was going
URL: https://yourapp.com/login?redirect=/dashboard

Attacker crafts:
https://yourapp.com/login?redirect=https://evil-phishing-site.com

Victim sees yourapp.com in the URL → trusts it → clicks → lands on phishing page
```

### Protection
```js
// ❌ Blind redirect
const redirectUrl = req.query.redirect;
res.redirect(redirectUrl);  // attacker controls destination

// ✅ Whitelist allowed redirect paths
function isSafeRedirect(url) {
  // Only allow relative paths — no external URLs
  try {
    const parsed = new URL(url, 'https://yourapp.com');
    return parsed.origin === 'https://yourapp.com';
  } catch {
    return false;
  }
}

const redirectUrl = req.query.redirect;
if (redirectUrl && isSafeRedirect(redirectUrl)) {
  res.redirect(redirectUrl);
} else {
  res.redirect('/dashboard');  // default safe destination
}
```

