# ATTACK 9 — Prototype Pollution

## What is it?
JavaScript allows modifying `Object.prototype` — attacker pollutes it to inject properties into every object in your app.

```js
// Attacker sends this JSON payload:
{
  "__proto__": {
    "isAdmin": true,
    "role": "admin"
  }
}

// After JSON.parse or lodash merge:
const user = {};
console.log(user.isAdmin); // true — prototype was polluted!
console.log(user.role);    // "admin" — every object is now admin!
```

### Real exploit path
```js
// Vulnerable code using lodash merge
const _ = require('lodash');
const userConfig = JSON.parse(req.body.config);
_.merge({}, userConfig);  // older lodash versions — pollutes prototype

// Later in auth check:
if (req.user.isAdmin) { ... }  // true for everyone now!
```

### Protection
```js
// ✅ Use JSON.parse with null prototype objects
const payload = JSON.parse(req.body);
const safeObj = Object.assign(Object.create(null), payload);

// ✅ Freeze Object.prototype
Object.freeze(Object.prototype);

// ✅ Use safe merge utilities
const { merge } = require('deepmerge'); // prototype-pollution-safe

// ✅ Validate and whitelist incoming object keys
const allowedKeys = ['theme', 'language', 'notifications'];
const config = {};
allowedKeys.forEach(key => {
  if (req.body[key] !== undefined) config[key] = req.body[key];
});

// ✅ Update lodash to >= 4.17.21 (patched versions)

// ✅ ESLint — flag __proto__ usage
"no-proto": "error"
```

