# ATTACK 12 — Dependency Chain Attack (Supply Chain)

## What is it?
Attacker compromises an npm package your app depends on — malicious code runs in your app or CI pipeline.

```
Real example: event-stream (2018)
→ Maintainer gave up package ownership
→ Attacker added malicious code targeting Bitcoin wallets
→ Millions of apps downloaded the compromised version

Real example: node-ipc (2022)
→ Maintainer deliberately added wiper malware
→ Deleted files on Russian/Belarusian IP addresses
→ Affected apps using vue-cli
```

### Protection
```bash
# ✅ npm audit on every install/CI run
npm audit --audit-level=high

# ✅ Lock exact versions
npm shrinkwrap   # creates npm-shrinkwrap.json with exact tree

# ✅ Verify package integrity
npm ci           # uses package-lock.json exactly — no resolution surprises

# ✅ Scoped installs — review what you're adding
npm info malicious-package  # check download count, maintainers, last publish date

# ✅ Socket.dev — scans for malicious packages before install
npx socket npm install <package>

# ✅ Snyk monitor — alerts you when new CVEs affect your deps
npx snyk monitor
```

